The paper focuses on developing an intelligent decision support system for stroke rehabilitation assessment using reinforcement learning. This involves identifying salient features of assessment and summarizing patient-specific analysis. The paper also discusses the importance of presenting contextually relevant and salient information and adaptation to develop a human and machine collaborative decision-making system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics).
